Hi, i was halfway through this then IE stuffed and i lost all of it so im doing it in NotePad!
I am going to explain the different ways to find colors.
Firstly we are going to use the most simple one, [code]FindColor[/code]
basicly this just finds the color at co-ordinates specified by XA,YA,XE,YE. It returns True if it gets the color and False if it doesnt. If its true then the script puts the coords into X and Y.In this function there is no tolerance here is an example of how it can be used
[code]program New;
{.include SRL/SRL.scar}
var
X,Y,XA,YA,XE,YE : Integer;
Const
Colour = 0;
begin
If FindColor(X,Y, Colour, XA,YE, XE, YE) then
Writeln('Found the colour.');
end.[/code]

The second function i will explain is [code]FindColorTolerance[/code]
It is the same thing as FindColor [b]BUT[/b] there is an extra parameter for the tolerance. Eg.[code]program New;
{.include SRL/SRL.scar}
var
X,Y,XA,YA,XE,YE : Integer;
Const
Colour = 0;
Tol = 5;
begin
If FindColorTolerance(X,Y, Colour, XA,YE, XE, YE, Tol) then
Writeln('Found the colour.');
end.[/code]

Thirdly is the [code]FindColorSpiral[/code] Function.
This function looks for a box of color starting at Xa, Ya (Top left) to Xe and Ye (Bottom right). Eg.
[code]program New;
{.include SRL/SRL.scar}
var
X,Y,XA,YA,XE,YE : Integer;
Const
Colour = 0;
begin
If FindColorSpiral(X,Y, Colour, XA,YA, XE, YE) then
Writeln('Found the colour.');
end.[/code]
Next is the most common command for finding colors, [code] FindColorSpiralTolerance[/code] this is the same as FindColorSpiral but it has a tolerance parameter. Eg[code]program New;
{.include SRL/SRL.scar}
var
X,Y,XA,YA,XE,YE : Integer;
Const
Colour = 0;
Tol = 5;
begin
If FindColorSpiralTolerance(X,Y, Colour, XA,YA, XE, YE, Tol) then
Writeln('Found the colour.');
end.[/code]
Finnaly I will explain the [code]FindColorSpiral2[/code] function. Its the same as FindColorSpiral but if there is a huge circle it just clicks in the middle. Eg[code]program New;
{.include SRL/SRL.scar}
var
X,Y,XA,YA,XE,YE : Integer;
Const
Colour = 0;
begin
If FindColorSpiral2(X,Y, Colour, XA,YA, XE, YE) then
Writeln('Found the colour.');
end.[/code]
I hope this has cleared up some questions about scars find color functions. I will soon update this with some more explanations of the functions but for now i hope a mod moves this!
